msgctxt "title"
msgid "Discord"
msgstr "Discord"

msgctxt "blurb"
msgid ""
"Discord is more of a community with video call features built in, than a stand-alone video call app. Initially a place for gamers to meet, chat and share, Discord has grown to over 150 million users"
" and its communities now include everything from book clubs, dance classes, study groups, anime, music, and more. Discord features text and voice chats as well as video call. The app is available on"
" Android and iOS, as well as a download on Mac, Windows, and Linux. Users can also login through their browser. Discord has had problems with toxic content harming its users, ranging from "
"harassment, human trafficking, and other online crimes. So if this is something your kids are using (it probably is), it's good to keep an eye out"
msgstr ""
"Más que una aplicación de videollamadas independiente, Discord es una comunidad con funciones de llamadas de vídeo integradas. Nacida como una plataforma donde los gamers pudieran conocerse, charlar"
" y compartir experiencias, Discord ha crecido hasta acumular más de 150 millones de usuarios activos y ahora incluye comunidades de todo tipo enfocadas a la lectura, la danza, el estudio, el anime, "
"la música, etc. Discord incorpora funciones de chats de texto y de voz, así como de videollamadas. La aplicación está disponible para Android e iOS y se puede descargar en dispositivos Mac, Windows "
"y Linux. También es posible iniciar sesión a través de un navegador. Discord ha tenido problemas con contenidos tóxicos que perjudican a los usuarios, desde el acoso hasta la trata de personas y "
"otros delitos cometidos en línea. Así pues, si tus hijos usan Discord (y probablemente lo hacen), será mejor que vigiles."

msgctxt "worst_case"
msgid ""
"Last year we found Discord didn’t require a strong password to login. When our research came out, Discord, to their credit, immediately changed their login process to require a strong password. Yay!"
" We love to see companies step up and make change for the better. Good work Discord! Discord does collect a fair amount of data on its users and says it can share that data with third-parties. "
"Discord says they do not monetize this data -- their business model is based on subscriptions to premium services rather than monetizing data for advertising. However, we found their privacy policy "
"to be pretty vaguely worded, which is a concern. They may not sell users’ data, however, it appears they can and likely do share data with many third-parties for only vaguely defined purposes. "
"Discord did let us know they are in the process of updating their privacy policy to make it easier to understand for users, which is good to hear. One final concern with Discord is its history of "
"malware and toxic communities. Discord users have reported experiencing harassment, abuse, and predators. Getting targeted with hate speech, getting harassed by misogynistic gamers, or accidentally "
"stumbling across a porn ring are all real concerns for people on Discord who aren't careful. Discord recently acquired a start-up that makes AI-powered software to detect and remove online "
"harassment, which could be a good step forward. However, other instances of AI content moderation in use in recent years have a questionable track record, so stay tuned."
msgstr ""
"El año pasado descubrimos que no hacía falta una contraseña segura para acceder a Discord. Cuando nuestra investigación salió a la luz, Discord cambió inmediatamente el proceso de inicio de sesión "
"para requerir una contraseña segura, lo cual dice mucho a su favor. ¡Enhorabuena! Nos encanta ver que las empresas toman medidas para mejorar. Por otro lado, Discord recopila una considerable "
"cantidad de datos sobre sus usuarios y dice que puede compartirlos con terceros. La compañía asegura que no monetiza estos datos porque su modelo de negocio se basa en las suscripciones a servicios "
"prémium y no en la publicidad. Sin embargo, su política de privacidad nos generó inquietud por su redacción bastante ambigua. Puede que no venda los datos de los usuarios, pero al parecer "
"probablemente los comparte con muchos terceros con fines definidos de manera vaga. La buena noticia es que Discord nos comunicó que está actualizando su política de privacidad para que resulte más "
"fácil de entender. Otra preocupación sobre Discord es su historial de toxicidad y malware en las comunidades. Los usuarios han denunciado ser víctimas de acoso, abuso y depredadores. Ser objeto de "
"discursos de odio, ser acosada por gamers misóginos o topar accidentalmente con una red de pornografía son peligros reales para todas las personas que utilizan Discord sin el debido cuidado. Discord"
" ha adquirido recientemente una start-up que crea software impulsado por inteligencia artificial capaz de detectar y eliminar los casos de acoso en línea, lo que supone un avance. No obstante, hay "
"otros ejemplos de moderación de contenidos mediante inteligencia artificial en uso durante los últimos años con un historial cuestionable, de modo que debemos permanecer alerta."

msgctxt "how_does_it_use_data_collected"
msgid ""
"Discord states it is 'not in the business of selling your information,\" which is great. That said, the way Discord manages data is currently largely vaguely defined. One of numerous confusing "
"clauses is, 'We may also share aggregated or non-personally identifiable information with our partners or others for business purposes.' Discord says the do share data with third parties, including "
"service providers like Google, Stripe, and Paypal. Discord also let us know they are in the process of updating their privacy policy to make it easier to understand for users. This is good to hear "
"and will hopefully clarify some of the questions we found to be vaguely addressed in their current privacy policy."
msgstr ""
"Discord afirma que \"no se dedica a vender información\", lo cual es genial. Ahora bien, la forma en que Discord gestiona los datos está definida muy vagamente. He aquí una de las numerosas "
"cláusulas confusas: \"También podríamos compartir información agregada o que no permite la identificación personal con nuestros socios u otros con fines comerciales\". Discord admite que comparte "
"datos con terceros, incluyendo proveedores de servicios como Google, Stripe y PayPal. La buena noticia es que Discord nos comunicó que está actualizando su política de privacidad para que resulte "
"más fácil de entender; ojalá así se aclaren las cuestiones ambiguas del documento actual."

msgctxt "user_friendly_privacy_policy_helptext"
msgid "The policy is short and vague."
msgstr "La política es breve y vaga."

msgctxt "uses_encryption_helptext"
msgid "Discord uses encryption at rest and encryption in transit for all data."
msgstr "Discord usa el cifrado en reposo y en tránsito para todos los datos."

msgctxt "security_updates_helptext"
msgid "Discord pushes regular security update as necessary."
msgstr "Discord implementa las actualizaciones de seguridad necesarias periódicamente."

msgctxt "strong_password_helptext"
msgid "A strong password is required to login"
msgstr "Para iniciar sesión hace falta una contraseña segura."

msgctxt "manage_vulnerabilities_helptext"
msgid "https://discord.com/security"
msgstr "Véase https://discord.com/security/."

msgctxt "personal_data_collected"
msgid "Username, email address, IP address, device ID, and your activities within the services"
msgstr "Nombre de usuario, dirección de correo electrónico, dirección IP, ID del dispositivo, actividades dentro de los servicios."

msgctxt "biometric_data_collected"
msgid "No"
msgstr "No"

msgctxt "social_data_collected"
msgid ""
"Messages, images, transient VOIP data.\r"
"<br/>Optional: social network services data (Twitter, Facebook)."
msgstr ""
"Mensajes, imágenes y datos transitorios de VoIP.\r"
"<br/>Opcionalmente: datos de servicios de redes sociales (Twitter, Facebook)."

msgctxt "how_can_you_control_your_data"
msgid ""
"Discord claims users can delete any message they have ever sent. Once a message is deleted, it is permanently deleted from their servers. If a channel, a server or a user account is deleted, all "
"personal information is deleted too. However, we found the data retention section of their privacy policy a wonderful example of how a privacy policy can be made unspecific and confusing. Leaving it"
" here in full: 'We generally retain personal data for so long as it may be relevant to the purposes identified herein. To dispose of personal data, we may anonymize it, delete it or take other "
"appropriate steps. Data may persist in copies made for backup and business continuity purposes for additional time.\" While this may be rather standard privacy policy language, the vagueness leaves "
"us with questions like, what purposes are relevant?, how is anonymizing data disposing of it?, and that last sentence seems to negate the first two. Vague privacy policies leave us scratching out "
"head."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "track_record_details"
msgid ""
"In June 2020, Discord was identified as a favorable place to steal accounts. Discord also has a dubious track record of hate speech, abuse, and toxic behaviors on the platform. The company says they"
" are in the process of enhancing their processes to make it easier to report these types of issues. Hopefully this will be a good step forward to help improve their track record at protecting users "
"and their data."
msgstr ""
"En junio de 2020, se identificó Discord como un entorno propicio para robar cuentas. La compañía también tiene un historial turbio debido a los discursos de odio, los casos de abuso y los "
"comportamientos tóxicos detectados en la plataforma. Discord ha declarado que está optimizando sus procesos para que sea más fácil denunciar este tipo de problemas. Con suerte, este será un paso "
"adelante para ayudar a mejorar su historial en lo que se refiere a la protección de los usuarios y sus datos."

msgctxt "ai_helptext"
msgid "Discord allows AI chatbots. Discord recently bought Sentropy, a start-up that makes AI-powered software to detect and remove online harassment."
msgstr ""
"Discord permite los chatbots y ha adquirido recientemente Sentropy, una start-up que crea software impulsado por inteligencia artificial capaz de detectar y eliminar los casos de acoso en línea."

